gomodel:SYNGO_4642  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2. immunoperoxidase labeling of ICAM-5 in WT P14 and P28 mouse visual cortex shows localization to dendritic spines and putative filopodia, as well as dendrites and (to a lesser extend) glia.\n\nFigure 3. \"The immunogold reactivity for ICAM-5 also showed the expected distribution in neuronal cell bodies, dendrites, dendritic protrusions and glial profiles, including Iba-1 labeled microglial elements (Figure 3A-D). As the immunogold labeling affords a precise localization, this analysis also revealed that ICAM-5 predominantly localizes to the plasma membrane of neuronal and glial profiles\". Experimental description: \"Figure 2. ICAM-5 Labeling in WT P14 and P28 mouse visual cortex\"\n\nTable 1, antibody for ICAM-5;\n\nIntercellular adhesion molecule 5; Polyclonal antibody; Antiserum produced in rabbit, corresponding to the peptide sequence: AEGGAETPGT AESPADGEVF AIQLTSS which pertains to the last 17 amino acids in the C-terminus of mouse telencephalon.\n\nGift from Dr. Yoshihara; Brain Science Institute/Institute of Physical and Chemical Research (Wako City, Japan)\n\nYoshihara et. al., Neuron, 12(3), 541 (1994)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4642" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

